<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="c7fd488171dcc9f20d438c7ec38b96d2" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magic/articles/articles.php'>Video Games and Movies</option><option value='/wars/articles/articles.php'>Wizards Minis</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> LOTR Q&A Rulings from 05/06/04<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.88)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=617'>Enrique "Max of Tat" Huerta</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=617&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> May 20, 2004</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> Hello All!!<br />
<br />
   In case you didn&#39;t know, the CRD has basically been replaced with the new Comprehensive Rulebook ver 3.0. It&#39;s nice to have a single document that can answer all your rules questions. (Gee... I hope I&#39;m not out of a job!) There is still a CRD with the x-list and one minor entry.<br />
<br />
   Speaking of the x-list, Filbert and O Elbereth! are off the list. No new cards were added. Let&#39;s see how much of an impact the return of those cards has on the game.<br />
<br />
- Enrique<br />
<br />
<h3>Questions about Card Rulings:</h3><br />
<b>I&#39;ve seen your articles regarding Q&A&#39;s so I have a question to ask. Corsair Marauder says &#39;when you play this minion, if you can spot another corsair, you may discard a possession to add 2 (raider) tokens to a card that already has a (raider) token on it.&#39; Is he allowed to discard Free Peoples possessions? The question only arises because there are other minion cards that specify &#39;discard a Free Peoples possession&#39; while this card only says &#39;discard a possession&#39; and since corsairs have many possessions it seems as if you discard one of your own possessions. Thanks [Han Solo]</b><br />
<br />
Because it does not specify Shadow or Free Peoples, you&#39;re allowed to discard either type of possession.<br />
<br />
<b>Aggression-If my Gimli, Counter of Foes with 2 wounds plus 4 aggression in play...do I draw 7 cards or 4 ?? Here is Good Rock - When I stack a free poeple card on it, do i my Gimli, FC gets damage +1 permanently??? Or is the effect last during that skirmish only???? Honed - Is there limit to Strength addition to a dwarf ??? TQ. [Bobcat64]</b> <br />
<br />
1. Agression is a Fellowship action and is limited by the Rule of 4. You&#39;re only allowed to draw or take into had up to 4 cards during each Fellowship phase.<br />
<br />
2. Here is Good Rock is a Skirmish action and would only last for the duration of that skirmish.<br />
<br />
3. Theoretically, there is a limit. However, for the purposes of your question, no there is not a limit. If Gimli is Damage +6, Honed will make him Strength +6. If he&#39;s Damage +20, Strength +20. There is no limit to the Stength added, just a limit to how big you can make Gimli. (= <br />
<br />
<b>the new reflections card galadriel, bearer of wisdom states that if she bear the one ring or an artifact she is resistance +1 for each other (elven) companion,.my question is that if i give her the one ring and an artifact would her resistance be +2 per (elven) companion? EX: Galadriel has nenya and the one ring and spots glorfindel, and arwen, would her resistance be +4 or +2? [The easterling] </b><br />
<br />
No, she would only be +1 no matter how many One Rings or artifacts she bore. (And no, you can&#39;t have more than 1 One Ring in your deck.)<br />
<br />
<h3>Questions about Game/Tournament Rulings:</h3><br />
<b>HI. I have two similar cuestions (about LOTR trade card game): <br />
1.- On the Slags Mounds Frodo is killed and I translate the One Ring to Sam... do I have to put a burden to Sam becouse Frodo has been killed or no? <br />
3.- An orc overhelms to Frodo and there&#39;s an Orc Officer in play. The One Ring goes to Sam...do I have to put the three burdens to Sam or no? <br />
Thanks [Balder]</b><br />
<br />
1. No. When Frodo is killed, the Slag Mounds is a mandatory action. It would occur before Sam&#39;s optional response to Frodo being killed. The Slag Mounds would try to add a burden, but (since there isn&#39;t a Ring-bearer at this moment in time) it would have no effect. Then Sam would become the Ring-bearer.<br />
<br />
2. For the same reason, no. The Orc Officer is also a madatory action and it occurs before Sam&#39;s optional response.<br />
<br />
<b>If Boromir, Bearer of Council is wearing Armor, and at the start of his skirmish I choose wounds, he only takes one, correct? If he only has one wound to give, and is wearing armor,can I still choose that option? Or does the presence of the armor somehow force me to choose burdens, since Boromir cannot be wounded twice??? <br />
<br />
On (what I think is) a similar note, the Crashed gate allows the Freep to choose which option on the site. The Online game forces you to give your opponent a site if you cannot add 3 burdens. Is this correct? Since the site text is NOT a cost, I need not fufill all of the chosen option, I simply pick one and execute as much of that option as possible, for instance only adding 2 threats because of my fellowship size. Similary if my opponent is on Site 1 (somehow), do I have to add three threats? <br />
<br />
Does the inability to fufill all of one choice force a player into the other? Thanks! [HungTroll]</b><br />
<br />
The rule that governs these situations is as follows:<br />
<i>&quot;If the effect of a card or special ability requires you to choose one of two different actions, you must choose an action that you are fully capable of performing (if possible).&quot; </i><br />
[Comprehensive Rulebook 3.0, pg 30]<br />
<br />
You must choose can effect that you can fully complete. If you cannot fully wound Boromir twice, you must add burdens. If you cannot add 3 threats, you must let your opponent control a site.<br />
<br />
<b>I&#39;m playing dunlend for the first time, and have a question about hillman mob. it says that when it wins, i play a minion that is fierce and damage plus 1. some people are telling me that because the second minion is played during the skirmish phase, they only have to fight them once, during the fierce skirmish phase. i say that the free peoples have to fight that second minion twice. which is correct? [mike schroeder]</b><br />
<br />
You do not face the new minion twice. The other people are correct. Only characters that are in play during the first assignment phase are can be assigned to skirmishes. When the new minion comes into play, it&#39;s too late for them to be assigned to a skirmish. (The same would be true for a companion played with Theoden, Tall and Proud&#39;s gametext.) After the first round of skirmish phases are done, there is the foerce assignment phase. Since the new minion is fierce it would be assigned to a skirmish now. Once the fierce skrimish phases are over, there is no more skirmishing (except for Return to Its Master) no matter how fierce you are or how many skimrish you&#39;ve actually had at this site.<br />
<br />
